# Config Client

The config client can be used by importing sdc-clients.Config, creating a new
Config object and utilizing it's properties as though it were a simple JS
object.

    var cfg = new Config({svc: 'capi', ufdsargs: ufds});
    var url = cfg.url;

The Config client will search the UFDS instance pointed at by **ufdsargs** for
objectclass=config entries at the LDAP tree beginning with
svc=*svc*,ou=config,o=smartdc

The Config client respects datacentre and host scoping through the **dc** and
**host** properties, and will populate it's own properties with fallthrough. For
instance, if we have the following ldap entries:

    # dc=us-west-1,svc=capi,ou=config,o=smartdc
    dn: dc=us-west-1,svc=capi,ou=config,o=smartdc
    svc: capi
    url: http://10.99.99.5
    objectclass: config

    # svc=capi,ou=config,o=smartdc
    dn: svc=capi,ou=config,o=smartdc
    svc: capi
    url: http://192.168.1.5
    foo: bar
    objectclass: config

calling the "foo" property of a Config object instantiated with *us-west-1*
scope will yield 'bar', and calling the "url" property will yield
"http://10.99.99.5", whereas calling it on a non-scoped Config object would
yield "http://192.168.1.5"

The Config client also supports ldap referrals both to other hosts as well
as other branches of the tree. Given the following ldap entry

    dn: ref=mapi, svc=capi, ou=config, o=smartdc
    ref: svc=mapi,ou=config,o=smartdc
    objectclass: referral

A Config object with **svc** of *capi* could access the *mapi* properties
through  it's own *mapi* property

  var mapiurl = config.mapi.url;

## Config(options)

Creates a UFDS Config client instance.

Options must be an object that contains

|| *Name* || *Type* || *Description* ||
|| svc || String || name of the service to fetch configuration for ||
|| ufdsargs || object || ufds options as documented in the UFDS section above ||
|| dc || String || optional* the datacentre name, if used for scoping ||
|| host || String || optional* the host name, if used for scoping ||
|| nofollowref || Object or *false* || optional* do not follow ldap referrals (to other services) ||

Config objects are a subclass of **EventEmitter**. On changes in LDAP state
which affect the object, it will update it's properties and emit *"update"*


## insert(cfg)

Insert the properties in *cfg* in to the configuration database

|| *Name* || *Type* || *Description* ||
|| cfg || Object || object containing the key:value pairs of properties to insert ( must be of the form key:*String* ) ||


